Following the guidelines by the Presidential Task Force on Covid-19, President Muhammadu Buhari and his family had the Eid-el-Fitr prayers at hiss residence Presidential Villa, Abuja Sunday morning.
He had announced earlier that no visitors would be allowed to visit during the celebration, and he urged other Muslims to stay at home to observe for the Ramadan ritual.
But many states in the north, including Jigawa, Bauch, Benue, Nasarawa allowed worshippers to congregate as usual for the prayer.